'''Matías Nicolás Viña Susperreguy''' (born 9 November 1997) is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or [[left wing-back]] for [[AFA Liga Profesional de Fútbol]] club [[Club Atletico River Plate|River Plate]], on loan from [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|matias-nicolas-vina-susperreguy/471082}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Nacional===
Viña was signed by [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]] in 2015 when he was 17 years old. He joined the Fourth Division and had the opportunity to practice with the professional team.<ref>{{cite web|first=Sebastián|last=Amaya|url=http://www.referi.uy/una-nueva-generacion-cracks-n1024304|title=¿Una nueva generación de cracks?|website=Referí|date=2 February 2017|access-date=4 February 2017|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tenfield.com.uy/nacional-de-pena-en-el-clasico-de-las-amarillas/|title=Nacional: clásico en la mira con De Pena|website=Tenfield|date=27 April 2015|language=es}}</ref> One year later, Viña achieved his first minutes with the club's reserve team, having played eight games in the Third Division.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nacional.uy/futbol/formativas/noticias/item/reserva-la-campana-tricolor-en-el-campeonato-uruguayo-especial-2016.html|title= Reserva: La campaña tricolor en el Campeonato Uruguayo Especial 2016|publisher=Club Nacional de Football|date=19 December 2016|language=es|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309030702/https://www.nacional.uy/futbol/formativas/noticias/item/reserva-la-campana-tricolor-en-el-campeonato-uruguayo-especial-2016.html|archive-date=9 March 2021}}</ref>

===Palmeiras===
On 31 January 2020, Viña left the club to join [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] side [[Palmeiras]], where he won the [[Treble (association football)|treble]]<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bengtson|first=Kristian|date=9 March 2021|title=Palmeiras 2-0 Grêmio – the Treble is complete!|url=https://anythingpalmeiras.com/2021/03/08/palmeiras-2-0-gremio-the-treble-is-complete/|access-date=28 October 2021|website=ANYTHING PALMEIRAS|language=en}}</ref> consisting of the [[Campeonato Paulista]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/reportagens-especiais/palmeiras-campeao-paulista-2020/|title = Enfim, campeão: Com jovens da base decisivos, um novo Palmeiras sem tantos medalhões quebra a sina de 12 anos sem o Paulista}}</ref> [[Copa Libertadores]]<ref>{{Cite news|title=Palmeiras win Copa in dramatic fashion|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/55874806|access-date=28 October 2021}}</ref> and [[Copa do Brasil]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/america/20200201/473233987659/el-palmeiras-anuncia-fichaje-del-uruguayo-matias-vina.html|title=El Palmeiras anuncia fichaje del uruguayo Matías Viña|publisher=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|date=1 February 2020|access-date=5 February 2020|language=es}}</ref>

===Roma===
In August 2021, he signed for [[Serie A]] club [[A.S. Roma]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/el-uruguayo-matias-vina-fue-presentado-por-roma-este-domingo-como-nuevo-refuerzo-del-plantel-20218812830|title=El uruguayo Matías Viña fue presentado por Roma este domingo como nuevo refuerzo del plantel|date=8 August 2021|website=www.elobservador.com.uy|language=es}}</ref>

====Loan Bournemouth and Sassuolo====
On 30 January 2023, Viña joined [[Premier League]] club [[AFC Bournemouth]] on loan until the end of the season, with an option to buy for €15 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-30 |title=Viña makes Cherries move |url=https://www.afcb.co.uk/news/first-team/viña-makes-cherries-move/ |access-date=2023-06-24 |website=AFCB}}</ref> On 15 April, he scored his first goal for the club following his first ever start, coming in a 3–2 away win at [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tottenham 2-3 Bournemouth: Dango Ouattara's stoppage-time winner gives Cherries shock dramatic win at Spurs |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12855772/tottenham-2-3-bournemouth-dango-ouattaras-stoppage-time-winner-gives-cherries-shock-dramatic-win-at-spurs |access-date=2023-06-24 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref> He returned to Roma after Bournemouth opted not to make the transfer permanent and joined fellow Italian club [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on loan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-07-31 |title=Official: Sassuolo sign Vina from Roma |url=https://football-italia.net/official-sassuolo-sign-vina-from-roma/ |access-date=2023-10-12 |website=Football Italia}}</ref>

===Flamengo===
On 25 January 2024, Viña signed a four-year contract with [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]], for a reported fee of €9 million.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CR Flamengo|url=https://www.flamengo.com.br/noticias/futebol/flamengo-acerta-contratacao-do-lateral-esquerdo-matias-vi-a|title=Flamengo acerta contratação do lateral-esquerdo Matías Viña|trans-title=Flamengo agrees to sign left-back Matías Viña|date=25 January 2024|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=25 January 2024 |title=Flamengo anuncia a contratação do lateral Matías Viña, ex-Palmeiras |trans-title=Flamengo announces signing of full-back Matías Viña, ex-Palmeiras |url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/flamengo/artigo/_/id/13140653/flamengo-anuncia-contratacao-lateral-matias-vina-ex-palmeiras |access-date=27 January 2024 |website=ESPN |language=pt}}</ref>

On 11 August 2024, in a match against his former club [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], Viña suffered a serious injury which included a fractured [[tibia]], a torn [[cruciate ligament]] in his knee and a torn [[Meniscus (anatomy)|meniscus]]. He underwent surgery to fix the fracture in his tibia and reconstruct the anterior cruciate ligament in his right knee.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-08-15 |title=Com lesão no ligamento cruzado, Viña, do Flamengo, é operado e não joga mais em 2024 |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/flamengo/noticia/2024/08/15/vina-tem-lesao-no-ligamento-passa-por-cirurgia-e-nao-joga-mais-pelo-flamengo-em-2024.ghtml |access-date=2025-05-31 |website=ge.globo |language=pt-br}}</ref>

==International career==
Making his debut in 2016 for the [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay under-20 team]] in a friendly against [[Chile national under-20 football team|Chile]], Viña played in both the [[2017 South American U-20 Championship]], coming first, and in the 2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup, finishing in fourth place. He played 27 games for the youth selection, scoring four times.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/matias-vina-en-su-primera-experiencia-con-la-seleccion-mayor/|title=Entrevista a Matías Viña - AUF|website=www.auf.org.uy|access-date=17 January 2020}}</ref>

Viña made his senior international debut for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] on 6 September 2019, coming on from the bench in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ovaciondigital.com.uy/futbol/dejaron-debut-brian-rodriguez-matias-vina-uruguay.html|title=Qué dejaron los debut de Brian Rodríguez y Matías Viña en Uruguay|last=ElPais|website=Diario EL PAIS Uruguay|language=spanish|access-date=17 January 2020}}</ref> His debut as a starter came four days later, in a friendly against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]]; Viña played the whole 90 minutes in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/matias-vina-rindio-examen-y-aprobo-es-una-opcion-para-el-lateral-izquierdo-20199110252|title=Matías Viña rindió examen y aprobó: es una opción para el lateral izquierdo|last=Observador|first=El|website=El Observador|access-date=18 January 2020}}</ref>

Viña was included in Uruguay's 2022 World Cup squad and made two appearances in their three-game campaign, although they were both off the bench. On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

